node.text:
Have you ever made #juice at home? It's far more delicious and healty!

INGREDIENTS
2kg apricots
1 ½L water
700g (3 ½ cup) sugar
1 lemon

METHOD
Cut the washed apricots into small pieces.
Pour a liter and a half of water into a saucepan, add the sugar, and mix until melted. Pour in the cut apricots and mix. Add the lemon juice.
Mix and bring to a boil. Cook for 10 minutes. Let cool and blend.
Pour into glass bottles. Boil the glass bottles for 10 minutes and they will keep for up to 1 month

Ready in a few minutes, these #crepes easy and delicious!

INGREDIENTS
300ml (1 1/5 cups) kefir
2g (½ tsp) baking powder
1 egg
4g (1 tsp) salt
4g (1 tsp) pepper
100g (1 cup) flour
Spring onion
Dill
150g (1 cup) cheese
Oil
Cream cheese
Smoked salmon
 
METHOD
Add kefir, baking powder, salt, pepper, egg, flour, chopped dill and spring onions, and grated cheese to the kneading bowl. Mix.
Fry in an oiled pan.
Serve with cream cheese and smoked salmon.

You can make these buns for lunch or dinner, your faily will love them! 

INGREDIENTS
Dough:
½ kg flour
1 tbsp milk powder
4 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tsp salt
1 tsp sugar
7g dry yeast
Water
Egg
Sesame seeds
 
Filling:
2 red onions
2 bell peppers
Salt
Pepper
Garlic powder
Minced meat
Cheese

METHOD
Pour yeast and sugar into a glass of warm water and mix.
Add milk powder and salt to a bowl with flour and mix. Add the oil and the yeast-sugar mixture and mix again.
Keep mixing until you get a dough.
Place in a bowl, cover with cling film and let it rest until it is doubled in size. Cook pepper and chopped onion in a pan. Add salt, pepper, oil, garlic powder.
Add ground beef to one side of the pan, add more salt, pepper, garlic powder, and cook. Mix everything and continue cooking.
Divide the dough in two. Flatten each ball into a square. Draw several squares in the dough and add a little of the minced meat mixture into each square.
Add grated cheese to each square. Brush some water on the edges of the square.
Cover the entire square with the other piece of dough. Use your fingers to finish forming the squares and cut.
Place each square on a baking sheet. Brush beat egg on each one and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake for 20 minutes at 180ºC (356ºF).

You won't be able to stop at one!

INGREDIENTS
150g (2/3 cup) butter
400g (3 1/4 cups) flour
100ml (1/2 cup) milk
1 tbsp vanilla extract
50g (1/2 cup) powdered sugar
1 egg
1/3 tsp salt

150g chocolate
500ml (2 1/4 cups) milk
70g (1/3 cup) sugar
50g (1/4 cup) butter
40g (1/3 cup) starch
1 egg
Sugar
Raspberries for decoration

METHOD
In a bowl mix together flour, sugar, and butter. Add in milk and egg.
In a pan add milk, cornstarch, and sugar, cook on low heat until thick. Turn off the heat and add in chocolate, butter, and vanilla extract.
Divide the dough into two pieces. Roll out each piece and cut it into strips. Wind each strip on a cone.
Transfer to the baking pan and spread with egg and sprinkle with sugar, bake at 180’C (350’F) for 30 minutes.
Fill each cone with prepared chocolate cream.

A no-fail recipe to make great and delicious bread at home! 
 
INGREDIENTS
30ml (4 tbsp) olive oil
7g dry yeast
1 tsp salt
340ml (1 1/2 cups) water
600g (5 cups) flour

METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm water with yeast, oil, flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 2 hours (or until double).
Divide into three pieces and roll out them, then roll up in the shape of a baguette.
Transfer to the baking pan and let them rise for 1 hour more.
Make the cuts and sprinkle with flour.
Bake at 200 ‘C ( 390’F) for 20 minutes.

These #fritters are so creamy that you will forget your usual pancakes!

INGREDIENTS
250g (1 cup) cottage cheese
10g (2 tsp) vanilla sugar
50g (¼ cup) sugar
180ml (¾ cup) milk
25ml (2 tbsp) oil
2 eggs
150g (1 1/5 cups) flour
5g (1 tsp) baking powder
Apricot jam

METHOD
Add cheese, milk, egg yolks, sugar, vanilla sugar, oil to a mixing bowl. Whisk the mixture. Add flour and baking powder. Stir.
Whisk the egg whites and salt with a mixer and mix with the previous mixture.
Fry in an oiled pan.
Fill with jam. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

Quick and delicious!

INGREDIENTS
220ml (1 cup) yogurt
150g (1 1/4 cup) flour
1 egg
1 tbsp sugar
1 tsp soda
1/2 tsp salt
200g minced meat
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
2 tbsp shredded parmesan

METHOD
In a bowl mix together yogurt, egg and spices, add in flour.
In another bowl mix together meat with salt, pepper and Parmesan.
Into the pan on medium heat add a tablespoon of prepared mixture top it with meat and another tablespoon of the mixture.
Fry from both sides.

This method is genius! 😍😍

INGREDIENTS
 300g (2 cups) all-purpose flour;
 60g (¼ cup) butter, melted;
 100ml (⅓ cup+2 tbsp) water;
 Cornstarch.
 
METHOD
 Combine water, melted butter and flour to form a smooth dough.
 Set the dough aside for 20 minutes then roll into a thin rectangle and dust with cornstarch generously.
 Fold as shown on the video and repeat once more.
 Set the dough aside for 20 minutes then roll out thinly and cut into circles.
 Fold each circle and pinch with a clothing pin. Fry, dipping in hot oil, until the dough ‘blooms’, then remove the toothpick and cook until golden

This method to cook eggs is genius! You've never seen anything like this!

INGREDIENTS
250g (2 cups) flour
1 tsp salt
120ml (2/3 cup) water
4 tbsp oil
100 g melted butter
6 eggs

METHOD
In a bowl mix together water, oil, salt and flour. Let the dough rest for 30 minutes. Divide the dough into 6 pieces and roll out each.
Spread with melted butter and roll the dough. Roll out again for a little. Fry it in the pan on medium heat adding the egg into each bread.

Ever tried to fry pasta? You'll fall in love with this recipe! 
 
INGREDIENTS
Paccheri pasta
Ricotta
Cooked ham
Provolone
Parmesan
3 eggs
Breadcrumbs
Salt
Pepper
Oil

METHOD
Boil the pasta for 10 minutes and let it cool.
Mix ricotta, diced ham, cheese, salt, pepper, and parmesan in a bowl. Place the mixture in a piping bag.
Fill each piece of pasta with the mixture.
Beat 3 eggs, add salt, then dip the filled pasta in the egg and cover very well with bread crumbs. Coat twice.
Use a toothpick to check that the oil is hot and fry the pasta.

Have you ever made #juice at home? It's far more delicious and healty!

INGREDIENTS
2kg apricots
1 ½L water
700g (3 ½ cup) sugar
1 lemon

METHOD
Cut the washed apricots into small pieces.
Pour a liter and a half of water into a saucepan, add the sugar, and mix until melted. Pour in the cut apricots and mix. Add the lemon juice.
Mix and bring to a boil. Cook for 10 minutes. Let cool and blend.
Pour into glass bottles. Boil the glass bottles for 10 minutes and they will keep for up to 1 month

node.text:
Have you ever tried to make #piadina at home? 

It's super easy to make and perfect for a quick and tasty dinner for the whole family!

INGREDIENTS
400 g (3 cups) Flour 00
1 tsp salt
2 tsp baking soda
200 ml (1 cup) of water
30 ml oil (1/5 cup)
Cream cheese
Cooked ham
Rocket salad
 
METHOD
Mix the flour with the baking soda, add the salt, oil and gradually add the water while you knead the dough.
When you have kneaded the dough, leave it to stand, then divide the dough into four parts and knead 4 balls. Try to knead the balls in as few movements as possible, so that the dough does not become tough. Leave the balls to stand.
Roll out each ball and fry the piadines in a heated pan without oil. Fill them with rocket salad, cream cheese and cooked ham.

Don't they look delicious? 😍

2g (½ tsp) baking powder
1 egg
4g (1 tsp) salt
4g (1 tsp) pepper

Dill

Smoked salmon
 
METHOD
Add kefir, baking powder, salt, pepper, egg, flour, chopped dill and spring onions, and grated cheese to the kneading bowl. Mix.
Fry in an oiled pan.
Serve with cream cheese and smoked salmon.

You can make these buns for lunch or dinner, your faily will love them! 

INGREDIENTS
Dough:
½ kg flour
1 tbsp milk powder
4 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tsp salt
1 tsp sugar
7g dry yeast
Water
Egg
Sesame seeds
 
Filling:
2 red onions
2 bell peppers
Salt
Pepper
Garlic powder
Minced meat
Cheese

METHOD
Pour yeast and sugar into a glass of warm water and mix.
Add milk powder and salt to a bowl with flour and mix. Add the oil and the yeast-sugar mixture and mix again.
Keep mixing until you get a dough.
Place in a bowl, cover with cling film and let it rest until it is doubled in size. Cook pepper and chopped onion in a pan. Add salt, pepper, oil, garlic powder.
Add ground beef to one side of the pan, add more salt, pepper, garlic powder, and cook. Mix everything and continue cooking.
Divide the dough in two. Flatten each ball into a square. Draw several squares in the dough and add a little of the minced meat mixture into each square.
Add grated cheese to each square. Brush some water on the edges of the square.
Cover the entire square with the other piece of dough. Use your fingers to finish forming the squares and cut.
Place each square on a baking sheet. Brush beat egg on each one and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake for 20 minutes at 180ºC (356ºF).

You won't be able to stop at one!

INGREDIENTS
150g (2/3 cup) butter
400g (3 1/4 cups) flour
100ml (1/2 cup) milk
1 tbsp vanilla extract
50g (1/2 cup) powdered sugar
1 egg
1/3 tsp salt

150g chocolate
500ml (2 1/4 cups) milk
70g (1/3 cup) sugar
50g (1/4 cup) butter
40g (1/3 cup) starch
1 egg
Sugar
Raspberries for decoration

METHOD
In a bowl mix together flour, sugar, and butter. Add in milk and egg.
In a pan add milk, cornstarch, and sugar, cook on low heat until thick. Turn off the heat and add in chocolate, butter, and vanilla extract.
Divide the dough into two pieces. Roll out each piece and cut it into strips. Wind each strip on a cone.
Transfer to the baking pan and spread with egg and sprinkle with sugar, bake at 180’C (350’F) for 30 minutes.
Fill each cone with prepared chocolate cream.
